## Composition Examples

### Upload Newly Selected Images

The component emits the full list through `update:modelValue` and `change`; it does not emit a separate `add` event.

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import type { ImageUploaderFile } from '@talex-touch/tuffex/components'
import { ref } from 'vue'

const images = ref<ImageUploaderFile[]>([])

async function onChange(next: ImageUploaderFile[]) {
  const localFiles = next.filter(item => item.file)
  await uploadImages(localFiles.map(item => item.file!))
}
</script>

<template>
  <TxImageUploader v-model="images" accept="image/*" :max="6" @change="onChange" />
</template>
```

### Existing Remote Images

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const images = ref([
  { id: 'remote-1', url: cdnUrl, name: 'Cover image' },
])
</script>
```

Remote items without `file` are rendered and removable, but their URLs are not revoked by the component.

## Interaction Contract

- The hidden native input uses `type="file"`, `multiple`, `accept`, and `disabled` from props.
- The add tile is a native `button type="button"` and opens the input unless disabled or maxed out.
- The add tile is disabled when `value.length >= max`.
- Input changes are ignored when there are no files or no remaining capacity.
- New files are capped by remaining capacity and converted to `{ id, url, name, file }` records.
- New local previews use `URL.createObjectURL(file)`.
- The native input value is cleared after each change so the same file can be selected again.
- Adding files emits `update:modelValue`, then `change` with the full next list.
- Removing is blocked while disabled.
- Removing a local owned object URL revokes it, emits `update:modelValue`, then `remove`, then `change`.
- On unmount, all object URLs created by this component instance are revoked.
- Preview images use `name` as alt text and empty alt text when unnamed.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `modelValue` | `ImageUploaderFile[]` | required | Controlled image list. |
| `multiple` | `boolean` | `true` | Passed to the native file input. |
| `accept` | `string` | `'image/*'` | Accepted image types passed to the native input. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables adding and removing images. |
| `max` | `number` | `9` | Maximum total number of images. |

### ImageUploaderFile

| Field | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | Stable id used for preview keys and remove payloads. |
| `url` | `string` | Preview image URL. Locally selected files use object URLs. |
| `name` | `string` | Optional image name used for alt text and remove labels. |
| `file` | `File` | Optional original file for newly selected local images. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `update:modelValue` | `ImageUploaderFile[]` | Full next image list after add or remove. |
| `change` | `ImageUploaderFile[]` | Same full next image list after add or remove. |
| `remove` | `{ id: string, value: ImageUploaderFile[] }` | Removed id plus the next full list. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| - | - | `TxImageUploader` does not expose slots. Use controlled `modelValue` records for custom remote images; choose `FileUploader` when the upload row or metadata layout needs custom rendering. |

## Best Practices

- Use `ImageUploader` for image-only previews. Use `FileUploader` when you need generic files, drag/drop, file sizes, or an `add` event.
- Treat `accept` as a browser hint only; validate MIME, dimensions, file size, and content on the server.
- Keep remote image records stable with durable ids; generated local ids are UI-session only.
- Do not manually revoke URLs owned by this component; it revokes object URLs it creates.
- Store uploaded image URLs after successful upload and replace local object URL records with remote records in your app state.
- Keep `max` aligned with backend limits so users cannot select more images than can be stored.

## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/image-uploader/src/types.ts`, `TxImageUploader.vue`, and `image-uploader.test.ts`.
- **Verified coverage:** input attributes, existing remote previews, max-count truncation, disabled add/remove blocking, input reset behavior, object-URL creation, remove/change emission, and unmount cleanup.
- Lifecycle note: the component revokes only object URLs it created. Remote URLs or parent-owned blob URLs remain the caller's responsibility.
- API note: `ImageUploader` intentionally has no `add` event; use `change` and filter records with `file` for newly selected local images.

